My meme

I got an inspiration of my meme from the internet where it said Dont be mean, be above average, as somehow it helping with my self confidence and knowing being above average especially at 95% confident is very difficult.

library(magick)
#top left
mean_girl <- image_read("https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWRlZjZjNzctYzQwYy00YzdiLThkMTAtMjdmYzk5MWYyNjExXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTkxNjUyNQ@@._V1_.jpg"
                        ) %>%
                          image_scale(500)
mean_girl <- image_background(mean_girl, "black")

#top right
mean_text <-image_blank(width = 500,
                        height = 400,
                        color = "#ff3399") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Don't be mean",
                 color = "#ffffff",
                 size = 75,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#bottom left
normaldistribution <- image_background(image_read("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Standard_deviation_diagram.svg/350px-Standard_deviation_diagram.svg.png"
                    ) %>%
                    image_scale(500), "black")

#bottom right
above_text <-image_blank(width = 500,
                        height = 350,
                        color = "#ff3399") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Be above\naverage",
                 color = "#ffffff",
                 size = 75,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#top row
top_row <- c(mean_girl, mean_text) %>%
  image_append()
bottom_row <- c(normaldistribution, above_text) %>%
  image_append()

#mean girl meme
meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

image_write(meme,"my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

My inspiration comes from Halloween hoping to do a Peekaboo GIF with a ghost so that is why I inserted a ghost image and uses orange colour as the background.

library(magick)

#frame 1
frame1 <- image_blank(color = "orange", width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Peeeee", size = 100, gravity = "center")

#frame 2
frame2 <- image_blank(color = "orange", width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "ka", size = 100, gravity = "center")

#frame 3
frame3 <- image_blank(color = "orange", width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Boo!", size = 100, gravity = "center")

#frame 4
url <- "https://drawinghowtos.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/ghost-colored.jpg"
ghost <- image_read(url) %>%
  image_scale(500)

#frames
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, ghost)

animation = image_morph(frames) %>%
  image_animate(fps = 10) %>%
    image_annotate(text = "Hello!", size = 100, gravity = "north", color = "white")

image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
